<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>An Australian mum and entrepreneur has shared her quick and easy baking recipe to make a healthy Snickers mousse.</p>

<p>Rhian Allen, founder of The Healthy Mummy, revealed the recipe on her website and social media pages to her thousands of followers.</p>

<p>The mousse itself doesn't have any trace of Snickers chocolate, but instead replicates the taste to create a healthy alternative.</p>

<p>The five-ingredient recipe involves two steps and only takes a quick five minutes to make, so it can be prepared while dinner is cooking. </p>

<p>In an attempt to keep things simple in the kitchen, an Australian mummy blogger has shared her quick and easy baking recipe to make a Snickers mousse</p>

<p>The recipe is part of Rhian's 28 Day Weight Loss Challenge guide and is ideal to have as a healthy, sweet snack while losing weight.</p>

<p>'When dessert is this tasty, you won't believe that it's actually made with healthy ingredients that are good for you,' Rhian said online.</p>

<p>To make the mousse, home bakers will need ricotta cheese, cacao or cocoa powder, peanut butter, maple syrup and dark chocolate.</p>

<p>The first step simply involves mixing the ingredients together thoroughly in a bowl, followed by serving the mousse with extra dark chocolate pieces.</p>

<p>The mousse itself doesn't have any trace of a Snickers chocolate bar but instead replicates the taste to create a healthy alternative</p>

<p>Those part of The Healthy Mummy community gave the recipe a go for themselves and said the mousse is 'delicious' and is perfect for an evening snack</p>

<p>Those part of The Healthy Mummy community gave the recipe a go for themselves and said the mousse is 'delicious' and perfect for an evening snack.</p>

<p>'A simple bowl of snickers mousse tonight with some fresh banana,' Courtney wrote online.</p>

<p>'I love that once I've opened the ricotta, I know that I'll get to have this mousse a few times this week.</p>

<p>'If you haven't tried this amazingly simple snack then you need to jump right on it!' she said.  </p>

<p>Others online agreed and said they were surprised at how good the mousse tastes.  </p>

<p>Ingredients: </p>

<p>1 cup reduced-fat ricotta cheese</p>

<p>2 teaspoons cacao/cocoa powder</p>

<p>1/3 cup peanut butter</p>

<p>2 tablespoons maple syrup</p>

<p>1 tablespoon dark chocolate bits, plus extra to garnish</p>

<p>Method: </p>

<ol>
<li><p>Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well</p></li>
<li><p>Serve into cups or bowls and top with the extra chocolate </p></li>
</ol>

<p>Note: Eat immediately or chill in the fridge for 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving</p>

<p>Store leftovers in the fridge for 3 to 4 days</p>

<p>Source: The Healthy Mummy</p>
